Employee Group Types     Approvers     Clerical & Technical Employees  Administrators & Researchers  Non-Union Service Employees  Local 1 Service Employees  Service Employees  Non-Exempt Administrators  Student Employees             How do I access myTime?   NYU myTime is available through the Work tab on NYU Home. Click here to login to myTime.   Back to top               How do I submit a time off request?   To submit a time off request, login to NYU myTime through the NYU Home portal.   - In the Schedules section (upper right) click on the Request Time Off link.  - Next, click on the Create new Time Off Request link.  - Enter the Paycode (such as Sick, Personal Time, Jury Duty, Vacation, Sick Child, etc.)  - Enter the number of hours requested (for a full day, enter 7.0 hours)  - Click on View and Confirm details for this Time Off Request .  - Confirm that the information in the Request Summary tab (top of the screen) is correct.  - Click on Submit this Time Off Request (towards the bottom of the screen).   Back to top               What do I do if I can't clock in or access webclock or a hand recognition terminal?   If you are unable to clock in or out at your usual location, please contact your supervisor or HR Officer.   Back to top               How do I cancel a Time Off Request?   To cancel a Time Off Request in NYU myTime, login to myTime.   - In the Schedules section (upper right) click on the Request Time Off link.  - In the Current Requests section, click on gear icon in the Actions column.  - If you have a Pending Time Off Request , you will have the option to cancel the request.  - Click on Cancel this Time Off Request .     Back to top               How do I approve timesheets?   Approvers approve timesheets through the Time Entry area of the myTime Dashboard and clicking on Approve Timesheets . If you are a Time Sheet Approver, please be sure to do the following:   -View the eLearning course FIN 225: The Approver's Guide to NYU myTime (click here to read over available myTime Training material)   -Download and maintain copies of the following handouts:   FAQs for Approvers   Quick Steps for Approvers   If you require further assistance, contact the Payroll Service Center (212.443.TIME / 212.443.8463) or AskPayroll@nyu.edu.   Back to top               How can I get help with NYU myTime?   For any questions you may have regarding NYUmyTime please refer to the FAQs and Quick Step Guides available on this webpage in the employee group FAQs section (see above).   For further assistance related to Payroll issues, contact the Payroll Service Center. Send an email to the Payroll Service Center at AskPayroll@nyu.edu or call (212) 443-TIME (8463).   For other issues, please work with your Time Sheet / Time Off Approver and HR Officer.   Back to top               How do I view my vacation, sick & personal balances in NYU myTime?   You are able to check and verify your balance in the My Time section of the Time Entry area of the myTime Dashboard.Scrolld down the page and click on the Time Off Balances tab. You can refer to the Quick Steps and FAQ documents for your employee group, available at the top of this webpage. These handouts provide details about viewing your time off balances.   If you have questions about your vacation, sick, or personal time balances, please contact your HR Officer.   Back to top               How do I delegate timesheet & time off Approval responsibilities?   You can delegate approval reponsibilites in the Settings area of the myTime Dashboard by clicking on Manage My Delegations > Delegate Authority . For details, please read over page 3 of the FAQs for Approvers and view FIN 225: The Approver's Guide to NYU myTime, available in iLearn via the Work tab on NYU Home.   If you have questions about your vacation, sick, or personal time balances, please contact your HR Officer.   Back to top               What is the difference between a Time Off and a Time SheetApprover?   The main difference between a Time Off and Time Sheet Approver is as follows:   - A Time Off Approver approves designated employee requests for time away from work, which can include Personal Time, Vacation, Sick and all other reasons that require an employee to be away from work as scheduled.  - A Time Sheet Approver checks and approves employee time worked on a daily basis - that is the start & end time, lunch and other breaks, etc.   Back to top                                                                                  NYU Footer          Search      Directory      Campus Map      Events      Contact Us      Site Map      Copyright and Fair Use      Feedback         Unless otherwise noted, all content copyright New York University. Employee Group Types     Approvers     Clerical & Technical Employees  Administrators & Researchers  Non-Union Service Employees  Local 1 Service Employees  Service Employees  Non-Exempt Administrators  Student Employees             How do I access myTime?   NYU myTime is available through the Work tab on NYU Home. Click here to login to myTime.   Back to top               How do I submit a time off request?   To submit a time off request, login to NYU myTime through the NYU Home portal.   - In the Schedules section (upper right) click on the Request Time Off link.  - Next, click on the Create new Time Off Request link.  - Enter the Paycode (such as Sick, Personal Time, Jury Duty, Vacation, Sick Child, etc.)  - Enter the number of hours requested (for a full day, enter 7.0 hours)  - Click on View and Confirm details for this Time Off Request .  - Confirm that the information in the Request Summary tab (top of the screen) is correct.  - Click on Submit this Time Off Request (towards the bottom of the screen).   Back to top               What do I do if I can't clock in or access webclock or a hand recognition terminal?   If you are unable to clock in or out at your usual location, please contact your supervisor or HR Officer.   Back to top               How do I cancel a Time Off Request?   To cancel a Time Off Request in NYU myTime, login to myTime.   - In the Schedules section (upper right) click on the Request Time Off link.  - In the Current Requests section, click on gear icon in the Actions column.  - If you have a Pending Time Off Request , you will have the option to cancel the request.  - Click on Cancel this Time Off Request .     Back to top               How do I approve timesheets?   Approvers approve timesheets through the Time Entry area of the myTime Dashboard and clicking on Approve Timesheets . If you are a Time Sheet Approver, please be sure to do the following:   -View the eLearning course FIN 225: The Approver's Guide to NYU myTime (click here to read over available myTime Training material)   -Download and maintain copies of the following handouts:   FAQs for Approvers   Quick Steps for Approvers   If you require further assistance, contact the Payroll Service Center (212.443.TIME / 212.443.8463) or AskPayroll@nyu.edu.   Back to top               How can I get help with NYU myTime?   For any questions you may have regarding NYUmyTime please refer to the FAQs and Quick Step Guides available on this webpage in the employee group FAQs section (see above).   For further assistance related to Payroll issues, contact the Payroll Service Center. Send an email to the Payroll Service Center at AskPayroll@nyu.edu or call (212) 443-TIME (8463).   For other issues, please work with your Time Sheet / Time Off Approver and HR Officer.   Back to top               How do I view my vacation, sick & personal balances in NYU myTime?   You are able to check and verify your balance in the My Time section of the Time Entry area of the myTime Dashboard.Scrolld down the page and click on the Time Off Balances tab. You can refer to the Quick Steps and FAQ documents for your employee group, available at the top of this webpage. These handouts provide details about viewing your time off balances.   If you have questions about your vacation, sick, or personal time balances, please contact your HR Officer.   Back to top               How do I delegate timesheet & time off Approval responsibilities?   You can delegate approval reponsibilites in the Settings area of the myTime Dashboard by clicking on Manage My Delegations > Delegate Authority . For details, please read over page 3 of the FAQs for Approvers and view FIN 225: The Approver's Guide to NYU myTime, available in iLearn via the Work tab on NYU Home.   If you have questions about your vacation, sick, or personal time balances, please contact your HR Officer.   Back to top               What is the difference between a Time Off and a Time SheetApprover?   The main difference between a Time Off and Time Sheet Approver is as follows:   - A Time Off Approver approves designated employee requests for time away from work, which can include Personal Time, Vacation, Sick and all other reasons that require an employee to be away from work as scheduled.  - A Time Sheet Approver checks and approves employee time worked on a daily basis - that is the start & end time, lunch and other breaks, etc.   Back to top                                                                                  NYU Footer          Search      Directory      Campus Map      Events      Contact Us      Site Map      Copyright and Fair Use      Feedback         Unless otherwise noted, all content copyright New York University. Employee Group Types     Approvers     Clerical & Technical Employees  Administrators & Researchers  Non-Union Service Employees  Local 1 Service Employees  Service Employees  Non-Exempt Administrators  Student Employees             How do I access myTime?   NYU myTime is available through the Work tab on NYU Home. Click here to login to myTime.   Back to top               How do I submit a time off request?   To submit a time off request, login to NYU myTime through the NYU Home portal.   - In the Schedules section (upper right) click on the Request Time Off link.  - Next, click on the Create new Time Off Request link.  - Enter the Paycode (such as Sick, Personal Time, Jury Duty, Vacation, Sick Child, etc.)  - Enter the number of hours requested (for a full day, enter 7.0 hours)  - Click on View and Confirm details for this Time Off Request .  - Confirm that the information in the Request Summary tab (top of the screen) is correct.  - Click on Submit this Time Off Request (towards the bottom of the screen).   Back to top               What do I do if I can't clock in or access webclock or a hand recognition terminal?   If you are unable to clock in or out at your usual location, please contact your supervisor or HR Officer.   Back to top               How do I cancel a Time Off Request?   To cancel a Time Off Request in NYU myTime, login to myTime.   - In the Schedules section (upper right) click on the Request Time Off link.  - In the Current Requests section, click on gear icon in the Actions column.  - If you have a Pending Time Off Request , you will have the option to cancel the request.  - Click on Cancel this Time Off Request .     Back to top               How do I approve timesheets?   Approvers approve timesheets through the Time Entry area of the myTime Dashboard and clicking on Approve Timesheets . If you are a Time Sheet Approver, please be sure to do the following:   -View the eLearning course FIN 225: The Approver's Guide to NYU myTime (click here to read over available myTime Training material)   -Download and maintain copies of the following handouts:   FAQs for Approvers   Quick Steps for Approvers   If you require further assistance, contact the Payroll Service Center (212.443.TIME / 212.443.8463) or AskPayroll@nyu.edu.   Back to top               How can I get help with NYU myTime?   For any questions you may have regarding NYUmyTime please refer to the FAQs and Quick Step Guides available on this webpage in the employee group FAQs section (see above).   For further assistance related to Payroll issues, contact the Payroll Service Center. Send an email to the Payroll Service Center at AskPayroll@nyu.edu or call (212) 443-TIME (8463).   For other issues, please work with your Time Sheet / Time Off Approver and HR Officer.   Back to top               How do I view my vacation, sick & personal balances in NYU myTime?   You are able to check and verify your balance in the My Time section of the Time Entry area of the myTime Dashboard.Scrolld down the page and click on the Time Off Balances tab. You can refer to the Quick Steps and FAQ documents for your employee group, available at the top of this webpage. These handouts provide details about viewing your time off balances.   If you have questions about your vacation, sick, or personal time balances, please contact your HR Officer.   Back to top               How do I delegate timesheet & time off Approval responsibilities?   You can delegate approval reponsibilites in the Settings area of the myTime Dashboard by clicking on Manage My Delegations > Delegate Authority . For details, please read over page 3 of the FAQs for Approvers and view FIN 225: The Approver's Guide to NYU myTime, available in iLearn via the Work tab on NYU Home.   If you have questions about your vacation, sick, or personal time balances, please contact your HR Officer.   Back to top               What is the difference between a Time Off and a Time SheetApprover?   The main difference between a Time Off and Time Sheet Approver is as follows:   - A Time Off Approver approves designated employee requests for time away from work, which can include Personal Time, Vacation, Sick and all other reasons that require an employee to be away from work as scheduled.  - A Time Sheet Approver checks and approves employee time worked on a daily basis - that is the start & end time, lunch and other breaks, etc.   Back to top                                                                                  NYU Footer          Search      Directory      Campus Map      Events      Contact Us      Site Map      Copyright and Fair Use      Feedback         Unless otherwise noted, all content copyright New York University.
